Localization Discrepancy: The discrepancy is due to lack of sufficient evidence for accurate localization across multiple localization components, including lack of accurate GPS, lack of sufficient geometric signature of the road, lack of sufficient LiDar point features, poor IMU performance, etc. This discrepancy is geo-location related.

Planning Discrepancy: Autonomous vehicle is approaching the intersection while a front vehicle has already stopped at the stop line for the red light. The lane is very wide (as wide as two lanes) which caused the autonomous vehicle to decide to maneuver to the right side of the front vehicle and stop in parallel to it. This behavior was perceived to be overly aggressive by the safety driver therefore he disengaged the system as it started maneuvering to the right.
